<%@ Page MasterPageFile="~/Site1.Master" Language="C#" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="ProductFeatures.aspx.cs" Inherits="CommuterAlertProject.ProductFeatures" %>

<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" runat="server">
    <p class="titular-large" style="margin-top:25px;">
There are several ways to indicate your destination
</p>
<ul class="body-emphasis">
    <li>Long-press anywhere on a map.</li>
    <li>The map has train icons to indicate all of the
        train stations in the vicinity.  Long press 
        on any of them.</li>
    <li>Key in an address or intersection.</li>
    <li>Pick from an alphabetized list of train
        stations in the vicinity.</li>
    <li>Pick from a list of already-used locations.</li>
</ul>
<p class="titular-large">
Advanced Google technologies used which 
     minimize battery use.
</p>
<p class="titular-large">
Multiple ways to receive notifications
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Popup window</li>
    <li>Vibration</li>
    <li>Configurable voice text</li>
    <li>Alarm</li>
    </ul>
<p class="titular-large">
Other notable features
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Operates in the background, and issues an alert even if the phone is in sleep mode.</li>
    <li>Give your home nicknames to locations selected off of the map (e.g. - Home, Work, etc)</li>
    <li>Configurable distance sensitivity, as well as GPS sensitivity.  Tailor to your own conditions.</li>
    <li>Overlay help for easy usability.</li>
    <li>Train stations are identified automatically via Google Places Search.  All locations on earth!</li>
    <li>Train station database grows dynamically as you change location.</li>
    <li>Cached data for minimal Internet data usage.</li>
    </ul>
    
    
</asp:Content>

